President Obama spoke with President Recep Tayyip Erdogan of Turkey to express his condemnation of the recent attempted coup in Turkey and his support for Turkish democracy. He praised the Turkish people for their resilience against the coup and their commitment to democracy. President Obama also urged that the investigations and prosecution of those responsible for the coup be carried out in a manner that strengthens public confidence in democratic institutions and the rule of law. He assured President Erdogan that the United States is willing to provide assistance to Turkish authorities in their investigations.